<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="64.[189,310,815,841]" box="[189,310,815,841]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,815,841]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,815,841]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="64.[189,1399,862,1033]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[371,661,862,888]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[371,661,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Paracephaelis orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[671,763,863,889]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having larger leaves (13–18 × 
<quantity box="[1171,1304,862,889]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="cm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="5.5">5.5–8.5 cm</quantity>
vs 4.5– 10.5 × 
<quantity box="[271,362,898,925]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="cm" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 cm</quantity>
), larger inflorescences (4–8 × 
<quantity box="[714,801,898,925]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="cm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4–8 cm</quantity>
vs 1.5–4 × 
<quantity box="[937,1028,898,925]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
), longer pedicels (
<quantity box="[1242,1340,898,925]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long in flowering stage, up to 5(–8) mm long in fruiting stage vs flowers sessile), shorter bracteoles (ca 
<quantity box="[1331,1399,934,961]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity box="[223,342,970,997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
long), shorter calyx tubes (
<quantity box="[665,785,970,997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
long vs 
<quantity box="[885,1005,970,997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
long in flowering stage, ca 
<quantity box="[1331,1399,970,997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long in fruiting stage), fewer ovules per locule (3–4 vs 4–7), and ovoid fruits (vs spherical).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
